    "u i j represents the pointer to input no. j.",
    "The encoder network produces a sequence of latent memory states e j.",
    "The decoder also produces latent memory states, denoted by d i.",
    "d 1 corresponds to the trainable vector g. The computation of the pointer is parameterized by the attention matrices W 1, W 2 ∈ R dxd and an attention vector v ∈ R d.",
